Marvin Gayebot
===============

Software to control the Marvin Gaye robot from a
Raspberry PI running Isthmus (see http://eid.cool)


gpioloop - loops around on gpios, just for testing.

Gayebot inputs:
PIN COLOR    Function
 0  brown    GND
 1  red      VCC
 2  orange   head
 3  yellow   neck left
 4  green    neck right
 5  blue		 paw  right down
 6  brown    paw  right up
 7  red      paw  left  down
 8  orange   paw  left  up
 9  yellow   switch?
10  green    gnd
11  blue     pwm sound?

motor controls are simple H bridges.

RPi outputs:
SND+:  GPIO 18  = pin 12
SND-:  GND      = pin 14

par 1
IO_0: + GPIO 4  = pin 7
IO_0: - GPIO17  = pin 11

par 2
IO_1: + GPIO27  = pin 13
IO_1: - GPIO22  = pin 15

par 3
IO_2: + GPIO23  = pin 16
IO_2: - GPIO24  = pin 18

par 4
IO_3: + GPIO 5  = pin 29
IO_3: - GPIO 6  = pin 31

par 5
IO_4: + GPIO13  = pin 33
IO_4: - GPIO19  = pin 35

IO_5: + GPIO16  = pin 36  NC
IO_5: - GPIO20  = pin 38  NC

connect what to what? how to power the pi?
